  "texts": [
    "Figure 7 illustrates a matrix of co-relevance scores for every pairwise combination of input tokens in the matrix X.",
    "The light color along the diagonal indicates high corelevance scores whereas the darker colors indicate lower co-relevance scores.",
    "Some contextualized vectors in the output matrix Z will have strong mixes of co-relevance scores whereas others may have no co-relevance mix.",
    "Intuition: One can view vectors with a high mix of co-relevance scores as carrying signals about their relationship with other tokens in the sequence.",
    "Conversely, one can view contextualized vectors with no co-relevance mix as noise because they are standalone tokens that do not express meanings from other tokens."
